I can see the `ngap_gNB_handle_sctp_data_ind` function at line 265. The issue mentioned in the PR description is that there's a F1AP interface handling error between CU and DU causing message loss or corruption downstream of this function.

Looking at the function:

```c
static
void ngap_gNB_handle_sctp_data_ind(sctp_data_ind_t *sctp_data_ind) {
  int result;
  DevAssert(sctp_data_ind != NULL);
#if defined(TEST_S1C_AMF)
